{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WeskUkRZaTqNGvSnDoa5nM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Prometheus is listening on port 9090 internally, but the Service exposes it on port 8000. The deployment uses `--web.enable-lifecycle` which means I can reload the config without restarting via POST to `/-/reload`.\n\nThe headless service `rabbitmq-headless` has no ClusterIP, so individual pods are reachable at:\n- `rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.karma-rabbitmq-dr-security-e2e-advers-9db55a24-cluster-a.svc.cluster.local:15692`\n- `rabbitmq-1.rabbitmq-headless.karma-rabbitmq-dr-security-e2e-advers-9db55a24-cluster-a.svc.cluster.local:15692`\n- `rabbitmq-2.rabbitmq-headless.karma-rabbitmq-dr-security-e2e-advers-9db55a24-cluster-a.svc.cluster.local:15692`\n\nI'll update the Prometheus ConfigMap to add a scrape job targeting all three RabbitMQ pods via their headless service DNS names, then trigger a config reload through the lifecycle endpoint.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1465,"cache_read_input_tokens":32142,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1465},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8703155a-1cea-4b1b-b988-4b509d10f503","uuid":"ac645a71-dc89-426c-9ebf-7d8ec7718f5a","request_id":"req_011CcQ3HnMzcz1HU8yy6Ko57"}
